{"TopicId":217891,"ForumId":199,"TopicTitle":"AIRBRAKES deploy when performing roll","CreatedByName":"ShadowZone","CreatedById":112420,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T06:33:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ShadowZone","CreatedById":112420,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T06:33:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Microsoft Windows 11 Pro 10.0.22621 64-Bit | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 3900X 12-Core Processor (24) | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3090 (24340MB) | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E65459\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttach an AIRBRAKE to any part. Launch the vehicle. Press Q/E for rolling.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResult: AIRBRAKES will deploy with the roll input and even exceed their angle limit doing so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee video and bug package file for more details.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=BUG124.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BNuuQydPq1JMX74vlZEApBr06Qx7BEKBv2UTv95SLTL0mnHm04VQMNMz4s%2BUgpW7ZUclKgBmLY%2Bg9eCg0xZzN%5D%5Ba06ae1fcb61c697089c86e5e%5D%5Bdbf2e043a4adc9b5ff8b313b36d144cd%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EBUG124.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=BUG124_logs.zip\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BY4KL4fCrJ/%2BXGOliobbXWIxlMTDrtCrX8wnwG4eaThDrTpVUNyNmBjRL2Ob2vz906tlgYDbiHAdFsPHtL7uQJw==%5D%5B2326f60960762587de1887cd%5D%5B0defecb544bf8f49470c1fe69ab8081c%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EBUG124_logs.zip\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-09T13:00:53Z\u0022 title=\u002207/09/2023 01:00  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 9, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KC3","CreatedById":197222,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T11:43:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre they set to participate in roll? In KSP 1, you could use them for maneuvering and could toggle on/off with a right click.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ShadowZone","CreatedById":112420,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T21:21:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224296271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687520635\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KC3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, KC3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre they set to participate in roll? In KSP 1, you could use them for maneuvering and could toggle on/off with a right click.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is no option to set any control authority for airbrakes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jokers2","CreatedById":228032,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T04:05:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having the same issue.\u00A0 The fact that they would react to roll in KSP 1 but the option is gone in KSP2, BUT they still react, leads me to believe they are still using code from KSP1.\u00A0 Unless they\u0027re planning on adding control authority to airbrakes, how else does this happen?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-25T02:23:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw this also, made it very difficult to use them at all\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TripleStaff","CreatedById":59812,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-27T12:09:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis doesn\u0027t happen when they\u0027re in line with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E since they then won\u0027t affect the roll in any way, so they work fine for most rockets, but very annoying for planes...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-03T02:53:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed as of 0.1.4.0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}